{"parentUuid": null, "isSidechain": true, "promptId": "6c3a0b22-aa71-4abe-86b8-7ed7f2e35c75", "agentId": "a8bdfc72d1f506cf7", "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "Adversarially verify this finding about a design doc (the doc is at /tmp/claude-1000/-home-jleechan-projects-worktree-runner/8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b/scratchpad/gistfile1.txt; the repo is /home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner; you may use WebSearch/WebFetch and read files). Try to REFUTE it. Finding from the \"rust\" reviewer, severity major:\nTITLE: /dev/kvm existence check ignores permissions \u2014 libvirt backend gets selected, then fails at runtime for users not in the kvm group\nDETAIL: src/platform.rs line 179: `let has_kvm = std::path::Path::new(\"/dev/kvm\").exists();`. On virtually every Linux distro /dev/kvm exists whenever the kvm module is loaded, but it is `crw-rw---- root:kvm` \u2014 a user not in the `kvm` group cannot open it. backend::select (lines 199\u2013201) will pick Libvirt, config::generate will write a libvirt config, and the actual runner start will fail with EACCES much later, far from the decision point. libvirt adds a second layer: the user typically also needs the `libvirt` group and a running libvirtd, none of which is checked.\nRECOMMENDATION: Probe access, not existence: attempt `std::fs::OpenOptions::new().read(true).write(true).open(\"/dev/kvm\")` and treat EACCES as 'present but unusable' with an actionable message ('add yourself to the kvm group: sudo usermod -aG kvm $USER, then re-login'). Also check `which(\"virsh\")`/libvirtd socket before committing to the Libvirt backend. This belongs in a per-backend `validate()` (see trait finding).\nIs the finding factually correct and does the recommendation make sense? If the factual basis is wrong or the severity is inflated, refute it. Default to refuted=true only if you have concrete contrary evidence or the claim is unsupported after checking."}, "uuid": "2f7118c1-db8d-46ac-a1b6-2a00368290c0", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T22:01:21.755Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner", "sessionId": "8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b", "version": "2.1.198", "gitBranch": "fix/linux-runner-pre-job-hook", "slug": "velvet-wishing-cake"}
