{"parentUuid": "aa352d50-d6eb-455a-a337-56f096c579d3", "isSidechain": true, "agentId": "a8bdfc72d1f506cf7", "message": {"model": "claude-fable-5", "id": "msg_01XchLT1PjQmNjb94dhK5PDD", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_01HZdgERjJhxYoZhApdsBzdo", "name": "StructuredOutput", "input": {"refuted": false, "reasoning": "The finding is factually correct on every load-bearing point. Verified against the doc: line 179 is exactly `let has_kvm = std::path::Path::new(\"/dev/kvm\").exists();`, and backend::select (lines 195-201) picks Backend::Libvirt for linux+has_kvm with no access, virsh, or libvirtd checks anywhere in the doc (grep confirms zero occurrences of virsh/libvirtd/permission handling). Verified on a real Ubuntu host: /dev/kvm is crw-rw---- root:kvm (0660) and the user is not in the kvm or libvirt groups, matching the described distro default. The recommendation (open-probe treating EACCES as present-but-unusable, checking virsh/libvirtd before committing to the backend, per-backend validate()) is standard and sound. One minor overstatement: \"virtually every Linux distro\" ignores that (a) systemd-logind uaccess ACLs grant locally-logged-in desktop users rw on /dev/kvm even without kvm group membership \u2014 a live open() probe on this host succeeded via the ACL despite no group membership \u2014 and (b) Fedora/Arch follow systemd's v240+ default of mode 0666. However, this tool manages headless CI runner services, where logind session ACLs do not apply, so the EACCES failure mode is real in the actual deployment context on Debian/Ubuntu. Severity \"major\" is justified: the design commits to a backend at detect time and fails with a confusing error far from the decision point on the tool's mainline Linux path.", "corrected_claim": "The existence-only check on /dev/kvm (src/platform.rs line 179) and unconditional Libvirt selection (backend.rs lines 199-201) are correct as described, and the doc has no libvirtd/virsh/permission validation. One caveat: the claim that a non-kvm-group user \"cannot open it\" on virtually every distro is overstated \u2014 Fedora/Arch default /dev/kvm to mode 0666 (systemd v240+), and on desktop sessions systemd-logind uaccess ACLs grant the logged-in user access without kvm group membership. The failure mode is real specifically for headless service users on 0660 root:kvm distros (Debian/Ubuntu servers) \u2014 which is precisely the deployment context of a self-hosted runner manager, so the recommendation (access probe + virsh/libvirtd check in a per-backend validate()) stands."}, "caller": {"type": "direct"}}], "stop_reason": "tool_use", "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 2, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 1483, "cache_read_input_tokens": 61450, "output_tokens": 1826, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 1483}, "inference_geo": "not_available", "iterations": [{"input_tokens": 2, "output_tokens": 1826, "cache_read_input_tokens": 61450, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 1483, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 1483, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "type": "message"}], "speed": "standard"}, "diagnostics": null}, "requestId": "req_011CcfsvchzP9GGvPdMzpTSJ", "attributionAgent": "workflow-subagent", "type": "assistant", "uuid": "6c83760d-8ede-4976-9269-e12e26e0cfec", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T22:02:51.296Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner", "sessionId": "8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b", "version": "2.1.198", "gitBranch": "fix/linux-runner-pre-job-hook", "slug": "velvet-wishing-cake"}
